Unified discussion feed, upload fixes, editor UX improvements, and publish bug fix

- Unify challenge discussions with the main post system so students can
  upload media, comment, and like in discussions using the same PostCard
  and CreatePost components as the feed
- Add "Share to my feed" opt-in toggle so students control whether their
  discussion posts appear in the home feed
- Show challenge context badge on posts made in challenges
- Add challenge activity endpoint and expandable activity on profile
- Fix file uploads failing due to upsert:false, missing storage UPDATE
  policy, duplicate paths, and empty challengeId in video uploads
- Fix typing lag in block editors by applying optimistic React Query
  cache updates instead of waiting for API round-trip
- Fix challenge publishing not saving due to Zod rejecting null values
  for nullable fields; align status dropdown to use "active" consistently
- Add rich text editor hydration fix (immediatelyRender: false)
- Add prominent block inserter for empty lessons
- Add inline module/lesson title renaming with instant save
